						               													<description>STEPS GAMES are fun and exciting games in which players build structures by throwing wooden plates, called Stepses, onto a platform. The first player to get rid of all their Stepses is the winner!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sound easy? It's not!&amp;#10;One does not simply put Steps on the structure.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You should throw it in a way, so that it touches the opponent's Steps when landing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You need a strategy that works for you but against your opponents, one that you will constantly need to adjust during the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The winner must apply physics, engineering, logic, strategy, and a little bit of luck. All of which are useless without a well-aimed throw.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is an utterly unpredictable game where you won&amp;rsquo;t know if your next throw will work until you try it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You and your friends won't be bored while playing the game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The basic principle of the game is to keep the structure upright on your turn but unstable enough that it collapses on an opponent&amp;rsquo;s turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are six types of Stepses (for example rectangular) with different weights, sizes, and colors. The variations in size and weight mean that each type of Steps behaves differently when played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Want to add a personal touch to the game?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can have your name, motto, company name, or logo engraved on the Steps!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For a spectacular victory, take your Personal Steps and throw it with a flip so that it lands with your name up&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is how a Stepsman wins the game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play for any Company: Have fun with friends &amp;amp; colleagues, play with your family. It is interesting for children too, you can even play Solo!&amp;#10;If you play alone, you need to throw all the Stepses from the set on the playing board so that not a single Steps falls out of it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If at least one falls out, improve your skills and start again!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
